"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156943","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-12-02","<p>On 27 November we published the Winter 2013-14 Severe Weather Recovery Progress Report. This provides an update on the full range of support which has been provided to help communities, householders and businesses recover from last winter’s severe weather. The Report is available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/winter-2013-to-2014-severe-weather-recovery-progress-report" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/winter-2013-to-2014-severe-weather-recovery-progress-report</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2014-12-02T17:28:15.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156943/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156943/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156943/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-11-20","Floods","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how much of the Council Tax Relief Fund for people whose homes have been flooded has been (a) allocated to local authorities and (b) received by residents.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","215506"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156944","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-11-27","<p>The Government will make a decision in time for the provisional local government finance settlement in December 2014.</p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2014-11-27T16:46:20.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156944/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156944/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156944/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-11-20","Welfare Assistance Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when he plans to announce the Government's response to the consultation on the future of local welfare assistance schemes; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","215508"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156945","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-11-27","<p>All local authorities are bound by common law and must act reasonably and with due regard to their general fiduciary duty to tax payers. The compliance for awarding contracts by local authorities for any work, not just the sale for development of public land, is laid out in the Public Contracts Regulations. There is no day-to-day role for my Department to play in overseeing compliance.<br><br>The Secretary of State does have back-stop powers to intervene in a local authority under section 15 of the Local Government Act 1999 where he is satisfied that the authority is failing to comply with the requirements of Part1 of that Act - to make arrangements to secure continuous improvement in the way in which its functions are exercised, having regard to a combination of economy, efficiency and effectiveness.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-11-27T17:15:43.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156945/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156945/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156945/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-11-20","Land Use","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the role of his Department is in overseeing the compliance of local authorities with rules governing fair competition when awarding contracts for the development of public land.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","215428"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156946","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-11-26","<p>The procurement and award of this contract is a matter for the Greater London Authority and is not a process in which this Department has been involved.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-11-26T15:46:07.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156946/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156946/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156946/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-11-20","Royal Albert Dock","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what representations he has received on the award by GLA Land and Property Limited of the contract for commercial development of the Royal Albert Dock site to Advanced Business Park.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","215429"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156947","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-11-27","<p>Local authorities are independent employers, each responsible for the management of their workforces. This includes the pay and reward of staff and ensuring that they meet their duties as employers under equality legislation.</p><p> </p><p>The Local Government Association publish research on local authority workforce matters. In their most recent Earnings Survey, the Local Government Association estimate that in the 2013-14 gender pay gap in local government was one per cent. This compares with 4.3 per cent in 2010-11.</p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2014-11-27T16:39:13.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156947/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156947/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156947/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-11-20","Equal Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate his Department has made of the gender pay gap for employees of local authorities in (a) Stoke Newington and Hackney North constituency, (b) Hackney local authority area, (c) London and (d) England; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","215368"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156948","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-11-24","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the answer given on 11 Jun 2014 Official Report, col 143W.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-11-24T13:23:22.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156948/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156948/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156948/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-11-20","Tourism: Floods","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how much of the Tourism Industry Fund for Businesses in flood affected parts of England has been (a) allocated to local authorities and (b) received by businesses.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","215504"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156949","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-11-27","<p>Sport England’s flood relief fund has invested £1,195,800 into local sports facilities that were damaged as a result of the winter storms of 2013/14. All eligible applications were successful and the fund is now closed to new applications</p><p> </p><p>(a) £58,905 was allocated to local authorities, and £1,136,895 was allocated to community sports clubs, trusts and charities which operate at a local level.</p><p>(b) All Flood Relief awards made to date have been invested in sports facilities.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-11-27T12:10:34.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156949/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156949/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156949/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-11-20","Sports: Floods","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how much of the Flood Relief for Sport has been (a) allocated to local authorities and (b) received by sports facilities.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","215501"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156950","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-27","<p>The majority of adaptations to Service Family Accommodation (SFA) properties are carried out for the benefit of family members and dependants. It is not possible to identify separately those carried out for the benefit of injured Service personnel.</p><p> </p><p>In many cases, the MOD aims to move families into SFA properties which have already been adapted where this is appropriate, rather than understanding further adaptations.</p><p> </p><p>The number of adaptations to privately owned houses of personnel injured on operations is shown in the following table:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td> </td></tr></tbody></table><p>Number of Adaptations</p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td> </td></tr></tbody></table><p>69</p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td> </td></tr></tbody></table><p>95</p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td> </td></tr></tbody></table><p>73</p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15 (to end October 2014)</p></td><td> </td></tr></tbody></table><p>58</p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td></tr></tbody></table><p>Data prior to this date is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-11-27T16:10:06.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156950/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156950/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156950/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156950/answer/previousversion/30059","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-20","Armed Forces: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many housing adaptations his Department has carried out for wounded service personnel in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","215480"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156951","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-25","<p>Safety is monitored and regulated by the Defence Nuclear Safety Regulator, the Defence Maritime Regulator and by civil regulators. Deterrent performance is assured by the Chief Strategic Systems Executive. The Defence Nuclear Safety Committee provides overarching assurance to the Secretary of State on the adequacy of these arrangements.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-11-25T17:59:18.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156951/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156951/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156951/answer","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156951/answer/previousversion/30060","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-20","Trident","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department takes to monitor the safety and performance of the UK's nuclear deterrent and weapons programme.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","215481"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156952","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-26","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD), together with NATO and other international partners, is actively involved in developing knowledge of the effect that use of military sonar has on the marine ecosystem. Since 2008 it has used the Environmental Risk Management Capability (ERMC), a Decision Support Tool that utilises the underpinning research conducted over the past 20 years.</p><p>The MOD continues to fund relevant research including behavioural effects, marine mammal distribution, and marine mammal mitigation capability. The MOD also maintains a robust independent review process that ensures that relevant science is reviewed against the current ERMC practice and, where necessary, implemented. This ongoing process is supported by leading independent marine science organisations and the Government's Joint Nature Conservation Committee.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-11-26T16:11:29.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156952/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156952/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156952/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-20","Sonar","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what research his Department has conducted or reviewed into the effect of military naval sonar on the navigation of whales and other cetaceans since 2004.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","215488"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156953","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-26","<p>The table shows the number of personnel prescribed Mefloquine between 2007 and 30 June 2014 and how many were subsequently seen for an initial assessment at a Ministry of Defence (MOD) Department for Community Mental Health (DCMH) or admission to a MOD in-patient provider for a mental health disorder.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Number of personnel prescribed Mefloquine</p></td><td><p>Number seen for an initial assessment for a mental health disorder</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2007</p></td><td><p>1,163</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008</p></td><td><p>1,523</p></td><td><p>24</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>2,702</p></td><td><p>47</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>3,092</p></td><td><p>86</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>2,764</p></td><td><p>118</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>2,075</p></td><td><p>158</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>3,186</p></td><td><p>189</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014 (up until 30 June)</p></td><td><p>1,197</p></td><td><p>101</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Of those in the second column, seven had an initial assessment of Psychosis/Bipolar Affective Disorder.</p><p> </p><p>Like-for-like data before 2007 is not available. To provide numbers of personnel reporting with symptoms of hallucinations or suicidal thoughts would require the retrieval and review of individual patient records, which could be achieved only at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>The data on prescriptions for Mefloquine used in this response were derived from the integrated primary health record within the Defence Medical Information Capability Program data warehouse. It is not possible from this data to identify whether a mental health episode is associated with being prescribed Mefloquine.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-11-26T17:46:32.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156953/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156953/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156953/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-20","Armed Forces: Mefloquine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many armed forces personnel have been prescribed Lariam or Mefloquine in each year since 2000; how many such soldiers have reported (a) hallucinations, (b) psychosis and (c) suicidal thoughts; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","215391"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156954","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-25","<p>International funding to broaden the capability of the Ministry of Defence (MOD) Hebrides Range has been agreed, but I am withholding further details as disclosure would or would be likely to prejudice relations between the UK and another State. Separate work to upgrade the Remote Radar Head at Benbecula (North Uist) is being funded entirely by the MOD with no investment from other NATO or non-NATO nations.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-11-25T17:58:11.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156954/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156954/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156954/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-20","Military Bases: Hebrides","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which other (a) NATO and (b) non-NATO nations are investing in defence assets in the Hebrides.","false","Biography information for Angus Brendan MacNeil","Na h-Eileanan an Iar","Mr Angus Brendan MacNeil","215437"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156955","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-26","<p>A total of 321 locally employed Afghan patrol interpreters worked alongside the British Army between November 2013 and October 2014.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-11-26T16:10:26.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156955/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156955/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156955/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-20","Afghanistan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Afghan interpreters served alongside the British Army in the last 12 months of operations in Afghanistan.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","215465"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156956","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-25","<p>Details of Ministerial Meetings with External Organisations are routinely published as part of our Quarterly Transparency Return and can be obtained via our official report:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/ministers-gifts-hospitality-travel-and-meetings</p><p>The data from May 2010 to 31 March 2014 is published there. That from 1 April 2014 will be published in due course.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-11-25T17:01:03.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156956/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156956/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156956/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-20","Kuwait","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will list all meetings between Ministers in his Department and representatives of Kuwaiti defence companies in each of the last four years.","false","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","215410"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156957","Department for Education","false","2014-11-25","<p>According to the January 2014 school census, there were a total of seven schools with one or more infant (key stage 1) classes in excess of 30 pupils in Heywood and Middleton constituency. All of these classes had between 31 and 35 pupils.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>There were a further eight schools with one or more junior (key stage 2) classes in excess of 30 pupils. All but one of these classes had between 31 and 35 pupils.</p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-11-25T16:51:24.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156957/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156957/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156957/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-20","Class Sizes: Heywood","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many (a) primary and (b) junior schools in Heywood and Middleton constituency have class sizes in excess of 30 pupils.","false","Biography information for Liz McInnes","Heywood and Middleton","Liz McInnes","215476"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156958","Department for Education","false","2014-11-27","<p>Cabinet Office has recently consulted on draft Regulations to implement the new EU procurement Directives<a title="" href="http://3dcpri-papp09/new_parliamentaryquestion/215427-%20Steve%20McCabe/Draft/215427%20PQ%20Team%20QA%2025.11.14.docx#_ftn1" target="_blank">[1]</a> and is considering its response. The Cabinet Office plans to publish guidance on the new Regulations before they come into force.</p><p>The Department for Education is currently working with the Cabinet Office to understand the implications of these changes. The Department will communicate with local authorities in the spring so they are clear on the position. If necessary we will issue additional guidance in the spring.</p><p><a title="" href="http://3dcpri-papp09/new_parliamentaryquestion/215427-%20Steve%20McCabe/Draft/215427%20PQ%20Team%20QA%2025.11.14.docx#_ftnref1" target="_blank">[1]</a> <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/transposing-the-2014-eu-procurement-directives" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/consultations/transposing-the-2014-eu-procurement-directives</a></p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson",,"2014-11-27T17:33:45.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156958/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156958/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156958/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-20","Special Educational Needs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 11 November 2014 to Question 213558, when her Department's guidance on the impact of the 2014 EU Procurement Directives on the procurement by local authorities of school places for children and young people with special educational needs will be published.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","215427"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156959","Department of Health","false","2014-11-27","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 16 October 2014 to Question<a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2014-09-09/208753/" target="_blank"> 209550. </a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-11-27T17:25:30.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156959/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156959/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156959/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-11-20","Social Workers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment his Department has made of the number of professional social work placements, excluding the Step-Up and Frontline programmes, required in 2014-15; and how many places it expects to be provided by (a) local authorities, (b) third sector organisations and (iii) other organisations.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","215399"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156960","Department for Education","false","2014-11-27","<p>My Rt hon. Friend, the Secretary of State for Education has confirmed that she wants to see improvements to the quality of careers advice and guidance available to young people. We have issued revised statutory guidance for schools, which strengthens the requirement to build links with employers to inspire and mentor students. Schools are free to determine the most appropriate forms of engagement but might consider mentoring, workplace visits, work experience and employer talks. This will be particularly helpful in addressing stereotypes about specific career paths and providing young people with inspirational role models in a range of careers.</p><p>We have made significant progress in attracting more students to study science and maths at A level. Compared to 2010, we now have a thousand more girls studying physics every year and two thousand more girls studying maths. Our most recent A level results show that for the first time maths is now the most popular A level subject. The proportion of students entering A levels in biology, chemistry and physics has all increased too.</p><p>However, we need to go further. The Government has reformed the national curriculum and qualifications, to ensure that they enable young people to acquire the necessary knowledge and understanding to progress to further study and employment; we are recruiting top graduates into teaching by providing bursaries and scholarships in mathematics and the sciences of up to £25,000; and we are supporting schools through professional development and enrichment programmes, such as the Stimulating Physics Network and the establishment of 32 Maths Hubs.</p><p>The Government is also supporting Your Life, a three-year industry-led campaign, to ensure the UK has the maths and science skills it needs to succeed in a competitive global economy. The Your Life campaign will help to inspire young people to study A level maths and physics as a gateway to exciting and wide-ranging careers, and help employers recruit and retain talent, particularly women.</p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2014-11-27T17:35:43.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156960/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156960/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156960/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-11-20","Employment: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps her Department is taking to encourage increased female representation in (a) science and technology and (b) other traditionally male-dominated sectors; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","215369"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156961","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-12-01","<p>The estimated number and proportion of households which are fuel poor in 2012 under the Low Income High Costs (LIHC) Indicator in (a) Pendle constituency, (b) Lancashire and (c) the north west are shown in the table below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong><em>Estimated number of fuel poor households</em></strong></p></td><td><p><strong><em>Proportion of fuel poor households (%)</em></strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>Pendle constituency</em></p></td><td><p>5,552</p></td><td><p>15.0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>Lancashire</em></p></td><td><p>52,840</p></td><td><p>10.8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>North west</em></p></td><td><p>335,344</p><p> </p></td><td><p>11.3</p><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2014-12-01T15:21:14.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156961/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156961/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156961/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-11-20","Fuel Poverty: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what estimate he has made of the number of households in fuel poverty in (a) Pendle constituency, (b) Lancashire and (c) the North West.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","215375"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156962","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-11-26","<p>We recently consulted on the rules for the Warm Home Discount to apply in 2015/16. As part this consultation, we proposed amending the Industry Initiatives element of the scheme to allow participating energy suppliers to have the opportunity to provide rebates to residents of Park Homes. Providing support to park home residents in this way would be at the discretion of suppliers, who would also determine the level of support made available. The consultation closed on 13 November and we are currently analysing the responses. We expect to lay draft Regulations in early 2015.</p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2014-11-26T14:52:44.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156962/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156962/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156962/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-11-20","Warm Home Discount Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what estimate he has made of the cost of extending the Warm Homes Discount to park home residents.","false","Biography information for Julian Sturdy","York Outer","Julian Sturdy","215425"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156963","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-11-25","<p /> <p>There have been no statutory reports to the Health and Safety Executive (HSE) of an unplanned release of fluids, or of an incident that could have led to an unplanned release of fluids, in relation to oil and gas wells operated by Cuadrilla Resources in the UK since 2011.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-11-25T12:20:56.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156963/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156963/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156963/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-20","Cuadrilla Resources","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what instances there have been of well integrity failure at onshore oil and gas drill sites operated by Cuadrilla Resources in the UK since 2011; what the nature of such instances were; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","215513"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156964","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-27","<p>The procurement exercise to find a joint venture partner for Fera is underway. Defra Ministers expect to take a decision on the preferred bidder in the new year following the formal evaluation exercise.</p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson","215463 ; 215493","2014-11-27T14:07:13.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156964/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156964/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156964/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-20","Food and Environment Research Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether she has found a joint venture partner for the Food and Environment Research Agency; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","215498"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156965","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-27","<p>We have spent the following on improving air quality, including reducing nitrogen dioxide, since 2010-11.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Evidence</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Air Quality Grant</strong></p></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>£10,964,000</p></td><td><p>£2,361,000</p></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>£10,947,000</p></td><td><p>£3,078,745</p></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>£10,131,000</p></td><td><p>£3,100,000</p></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>£9,958,000</p></td><td><p>£1,000,000</p></td><td> </td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Evidence expenditure includes money spent on air quality monitoring as well as research work to gather evidence and develop methodologies for assessing and improving air quality. The Air Quality Grant Programme supports actions by local authorities to improve local air quality.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-11-27T14:06:04.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156965/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156965/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156965/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-20","Air Pollution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much her Department has spent on reducing nitrogen dioxide and improving air quality in each year since 2010-11.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","215499"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156966","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-27","<p>This Government plans to spend the following each year from 2015/16 to 2020/21 on capital investment to reduce the risks of flooding and coastal erosion.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total Capital </strong></p><p><strong>Investment</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>£395m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016/17</p></td><td><p>£376m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017/18</p></td><td><p>£383m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2018/19</p></td><td><p>£389m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2019/20</p></td><td><p>£396m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2020/21</p></td><td><p>£403m</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-11-27T14:07:50.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156966/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156966/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156966/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-20","Flood Control","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much her Department plans to spend on capital investment to improve flood defences in each year from 2015-16 to 2020-21.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","215496"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156967","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-25","<p>Following the tidal surge on 5 December 2013 and the winter storms of 2013/14, a total of 890 flood recovery projects were identified across England. A total of 844 projects involved the repair of flood defence assets, while the remaining 46 projects involved surveys, studies or actions relating to incident response.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As of 14 November 2014, permanent repairs have been completed for 814 of the 844 defence projects and there were 30 defence repair projects with temporary repairs. All the defences with temporary repairs also have contingency measures in place, which restore the standard of protection to pre-winter 2013/14 levels.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Going in to this winter, every community that was affected by the storms and floods of last winter will have the same or better standard of protection compared to the levels of defence they had before last winter.</p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-11-25T16:07:47.91Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156967/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156967/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156967/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-20","Flood Control","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many of the 890 flood defences damaged as result of the winter floods in 2013-14 have been repaired to date.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","215512"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156968","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-27","<p>Lord de Mauley, Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State in the Lords, received communications training in November 2014.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-11-27T14:08:49.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156968/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156968/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156968/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-20","Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, which Ministers in her Department have received media or communication training paid for by her Department.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","215497"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156969","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-27","<p>To date the Marine Management Organisation has made ‘storm damage’ payments to fishermen totalling £104,678.81 to replace lost or damaged fishing equipment with more selective gear.</p><p>However projects totalling £393, 161 have been approved and the remainder will be paid once invoices are submitted.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2014-11-27T14:08:25.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156969/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156969/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156969/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-20","Fisheries: Government Assistance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much of the Support for Fisherman Fund to replace lost and damaged fishing gear has been received by fishermen and businesses to date.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","215492"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156970","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-27","<p>The procurement exercise to find a joint venture partner for Fera is underway. Defra Ministers expect to take a decision on the preferred bidder in the new year following the formal evaluation exercise.</p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson","215463 ; 215498","2014-11-27T14:07:13.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156970/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156970/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156970/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-20","Food and Environment Research Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when her Department plans to make a final decision on the preferred bidder for the joint venture partner for the Food and Environment Research Agency.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","215493"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156971","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-27","<p>To date, £1,007,642 has been paid out to farmers and businesses in receipt of a Farming Recovery Fund grant against claims totalling £1,851,913.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2014-11-27T12:09:19.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156971/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156971/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156971/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-20","Floods: Agriculture","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much of the Farming Recovery Fund to cover the cost of restoration of agricultural land following the winter floods has been received by farmers and businesses to date.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","215494"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156972","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-27","<p>For the financial year 2012-13, Defra spent £2.5 million on badger control projects. This was inclusive of the costs of the postponed culling activity in 2012, as well as preparations for the 2013 targeted badger cull.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In the 2013-14 financial year, Defra invested £6.3 million in two badger cull pilots. The total cost of the policing operations for the two pilots was £3.5 million.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The implementation and policing costs for the badger culls in 2014-15 have not yet been finalised.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2014-11-27T12:10:01.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156972/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156972/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156972/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-20","Bovine Tuberculosis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much her Department spent on the implementation of badger culls for bovine TB control, and the costs to police forces of these culls in (a) 2012-13, (b) 2013-14 and (c) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","215462"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156973","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-26","<p>Net expenditure on bovine TB control in England, including expenditure on R&amp;D, was £91.2 million in 2010-11. In 2011/12, net expenditure was £93.6 million</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2014-11-26T14:20:15.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156973/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156973/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156973/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-20","Bovine Tuberculosis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much her Department spent on bovine TB control in (a) 2010-11 and (b) 2011-12.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","215461"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156974","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-25","<p>Preese Hall in Lancashire has been the only shale gas exploration well operated by Cuadrilla Resources to be drilled and hydraulically fractured to date. The Environment Agency carried out regular site monitoring and inspections to ensure it was satisfied that any environmental risks were being effectively managed. There have been no reports or any evidence of water contamination at Preese Hall.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In 2013, in the vicinity of Cuadrilla’s oil exploration well site in Balcombe, West Sussex, the Environment Agency investigated a local stream that turned fluorescent green. Analysis of the water samples detected ammoniacal nitrogen, butyl citrate and caffeine, all in very low concentrations. None of these substances have been used in drilling additives by Cuadrilla. The Environment Agency concluded that the green water was likely to be caused by the introduction of a dye into the stream, but the exact source remains unknown. Cuadrilla did not store or use any type of dye at Balcombe. The Environment Agency confirmed there was no environmental impact.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-11-25T16:08:45.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156974/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156974/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156974/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-20","Cuadrilla Resources","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether the Environment Agency has investigated any potential or actual cases of water contamination at onshore oil and gas drilling sites operated by Cuadrilla Resources since 2011; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","215514"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156975","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-27","<p>Guidance from the Veterinary Medicines Directorate (VMD) makes it clear that routine preventative use of antibiotics in livestock is not responsible use of these veterinary medicines. The VMD works closely with animal health organisations on the provision of guidance to farmers and encourages the veterinary profession to develop and implement prescribing guidelines.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2014-11-27T12:10:30.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156975/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156975/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156975/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-20","Livestock: Antibiotics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps her Department is taking to ensure that the use of antibiotics in farm animals is strictly for therapeutic purposes.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","215507"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156976","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-25","<p>The Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change Working Group II report makes a valuable contribution to our understanding of the impacts of, and adaptation and vulnerability to, climate change. We are considering it with keen interest and will take full account of it when we publish the UK's next Climate Change Risk Assessment in 2017, which in turn will inform the next National Adaptation Programme report.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-11-25T16:06:47.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156976/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156976/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156976/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-20","Climate Change","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether her Department plans to respond to the International Panel on Climate Change's report entitled Climate change 2014: Impacts, adaption and vulnerability.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","215495"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156977","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-27","<p>The Marine Management Organisation’s (MMO) use of unannounced visits and inspections is an important element within its compliance and enforcement activities. The use of unannounced visits is always considered carefully by the MMO and these are only undertaken when other forms of inspection would be less effective.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2014-11-27T17:32:00.91Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156977/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156977/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156977/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-20","Marine Management Organisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if she will review Marine Management Organisation policy on unannounced visits and inspections.","false","Biography information for Mr Geoffrey Cox","Torridge and West Devon","Mr Geoffrey Cox","215374"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156978","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-27","<p>The procurement exercise to find a joint venture partner for Fera is underway. Defra Ministers expect to take a decision on the preferred bidder in the new year following the formal evaluation exercise.</p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson","215493 ; 215498","2014-11-27T14:07:13.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156978/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156978/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156978/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-20","Food and Environment Research Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what bids her Department has received from the private sector to be a joint venture partner for the Food and Environment Research Agency.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","215463"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156979","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-27","<p>The Government’s position remains that we will bring forward a motion for a free vote on the repeal of the Hunting Act at an appropriate time when Parliamentary time allows.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2014-11-27T12:10:50.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156979/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156979/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156979/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-20","Hunting Act 2004","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what plans she has to bring forward legislative proposals to repeal the Hunting Act 2004 this session.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","215464"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156980","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-11-27","<p>Defra has received nearly 10,000 emails and letters in support of the campaign for a register of England's most important trees. Defra officials are already in contact with the Woodland Trust on this matter and a meeting has been arranged.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson","215454","2014-11-27T14:06:37.983Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156980/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156980/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156980/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-20","Trees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if she will meet representatives of the Woodland Trust and Country Living magazine to discuss a register of England's most important trees.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","215453"
