"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156982","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-11-27","<p>We are concerned by reports of damage being done to the wrecks of HMS Prince of Wales and HMS Repulse by metal salvage companies and recreational divers off the coast of Malaysia. We welcome the actions of the Malaysian Marine Department which impounded a vessel responsible for illegally disturbing and salvaging ship material for scrap earlier this year.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2014-11-27T14:20:26.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156982/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156982/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156982/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-11-20","Malaysia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what reports his Department has received of theft of metal and other valuable items from HMS Repulse and HMS Prince of Wales which were sunk off the coast of Malaysia in December 1941.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","215466"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156983","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-11-27","<p>As the details of where British Ambassadors and High Commissioners were educated are not held centrally, this information could be obtained only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-11-27T14:31:02.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156983/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156983/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156983/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-11-20","Diplomatic Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what proportion of British ambassadors and high commissioners were educated at (a) private school, (b) state school, (c) the universities of Oxford and Cambridge and (d) other universities.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","215445"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156984","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-11-24","<p>The Government remains committed to reopening the British Embassy in Tehran once we have resolved the outstanding steps required to bring the Embassy back to a functional level and made progress on arrangements for re-establishing a visa service in Tehran. We are in ongoing discussion with the Iranian government to identify solutions on both issues.</p>","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond","215451 ; 215452","2014-11-24T19:34:25.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156984/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156984/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156984/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-11-20","Iran","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent progress he has made on reopening HM Embassy in Tehran.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Alexander","Paisley and Renfrewshire South","Mr Douglas Alexander","215450"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156985","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-11-26","<p>The Government has raised the case of Ghonceh Ghavami with the Iranian authorities on many occasions, including most recently on 23 November. Both the Prime Minister and the Foreign Secretary have raised this with President Rouhani and Foreign Minister Zarif. We welcome news that Ms Ghavami has been released on bail. I met with the family on 25 November to discuss ways we can work together to ensure the best possible outcome of this case.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-11-26T14:28:18.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156985/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156985/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156985/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-11-20","Iran","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his Iranian counterpart on the case of Ghoncheh Ghavami.","false","Biography information for Naomi Long","Belfast East","Naomi Long","215448"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156986","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-11-27","<p>There are three boards within the FCO that advise on appointments for High Commissioners and Ambassadors, depending on the grade of the position. Some members of these Boards overlap.</p><p>4 Officers attended private school;<br>7 Officers attended state school;<br>We do not hold school details for 1 of these officers.</p><p>5 Officers attended Oxford or Cambridge and<br>7 Officers attended other Universities.</p><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-11-27T14:32:59.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156986/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156986/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156986/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-11-20","Diplomatic Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent estimate he has made of how many members of his Department's advisory board on the appointment of ambassadors and high commissioners were educated at (a) private school, (b) state school, (c) the universities of Oxford and Cambridge and (d) other universities.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","215447"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156987","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-11-28","I refer the hon. Member to the answer given on 27 November 2014 by my right honourable Friend the member for New Forest West (Desmond Swayne MP), the Minister of State for International Development (PQ215395).","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2014-11-28T15:04:35.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156987/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156987/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156987/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-11-20","Africa: Breast Ironing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department is taking to help end the practice of breast-ironing in Western, Eastern and Central African countries.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","215394"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156988","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-11-27","<p>We remain deeply concerned by Iran’s ongoing financial and material support for Hamas and other Palestinian rejectionist groups. The supply of arms to Hamas contravenes the embargo on Iranian arms exports established by UN Security Council Resolution 1747 and undermines prospects for peace and stability in the Middle East.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-11-27T14:26:41.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156988/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156988/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156988/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-11-20","Iran","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the extent of Iran's financial and material support for Hamas.","false","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond","215509"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156989","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-11-24","<p>The Government remains committed to reopening the British Embassy in Tehran once we have resolved the outstanding steps required to bring the Embassy back to a functional level and made progress on arrangements for re-establishing a visa service in Tehran. We are in ongoing discussion with the Iranian government to identify solutions on both issues.</p>","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond","215450 ; 215452","2014-11-24T19:34:25.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156989/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156989/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156989/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-11-20","Iran","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, when HM Embassy in Tehran will be reopened.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Alexander","Paisley and Renfrewshire South","Mr Douglas Alexander","215451"
